WEBVTT

00:00.820 --> 00:02.470
aka the smeeziest of them all,
The Turf Feinz.

00:02.670 --> 00:04.120
I'm with my brother.

00:04.320 --> 00:05.600
It's your boy Ice Cold 3000
of The Turf Feinz.

00:05.800 --> 00:07.080
Let them know. Let them know.
Let them know.

00:07.280 --> 00:08.390
- And you would not believe...
- Uh-huh.

00:08.590 --> 00:09.480
- ...what happened...
- What happened?

00:09.680 --> 00:10.740
- ...last week...
- Yeah.

00:10.940 --> 00:11.680
- ...on <i>Blindspotting.</i>
- Ooh!

00:11.870 --> 00:14.050
[hip-hop music plays]

00:14.250 --> 00:15.850
My pops, he's a chef at, uh--

00:16.050 --> 00:17.620
you know that spot
Brewer's Feast?

00:17.820 --> 00:20.210
I worked the line under my pops
as a teenager.

00:20.410 --> 00:22.100
I'm talking about squad cars

00:22.300 --> 00:23.710
all in front
of my pops' restaurant.

00:23.910 --> 00:26.470
And then I'm walking out
in front of white table diners

00:26.670 --> 00:27.520
in cuffs.

00:27.720 --> 00:30.370
♪ ♪

00:30.570 --> 00:31.480
[Janelle] <i>Oh, look,</i>
<i>your brother made it.</i>

00:31.680 --> 00:33.760
Oh, absolutely not.

00:33.960 --> 00:35.220
Get back in your car
and fuck off now

00:35.420 --> 00:36.770
before he sees you.

00:36.970 --> 00:38.810
<i>Fuck, it feels so good</i>
<i>to be out</i>

00:39.010 --> 00:41.900
<i>doing some</i>
<i>normal-ass shit, girl.</i>

00:42.100 --> 00:44.600
- Ashley!
- It's not what you think.

00:44.800 --> 00:47.080
Bitch, you cheated on my
brother while he is in prison.

00:47.280 --> 00:49.190
Ashley, that's not true, is it?

00:49.390 --> 00:50.890
And I'll tell Miles myself.

00:51.090 --> 00:53.330
Just-just please at least
let me tell him myself.

00:53.530 --> 00:55.120
You just did.

00:58.740 --> 01:01.590
[soft music plays]

01:01.790 --> 01:04.650
♪ ♪

01:06.700 --> 01:08.340
[buzzer blares]

01:08.540 --> 01:10.020
[person coughing]

01:10.220 --> 01:12.300
[indistinct chatter]

01:12.500 --> 01:14.610
Yo, yo, yo! Miles Turner.

01:14.810 --> 01:16.960
Yeah?

01:17.160 --> 01:19.070
Luckiest day of your life.
Pack your shit up.

01:19.270 --> 01:20.270
Why, y'all gonna transfer me?

01:20.470 --> 01:21.940
Please don't transfer me, man.

01:22.140 --> 01:23.460
M-my whole family's here.
We can't take this.

01:23.660 --> 01:24.880
Hey, man, I'm just
following orders, man.

01:25.080 --> 01:26.550
I don't give a shit.

01:26.750 --> 01:28.210
But your arresting officers
of the Oakland PD,

01:28.410 --> 01:30.280
they were caught planting
evidence in their cases.

01:30.480 --> 01:31.970
So I'ma go ahead and guess
that your case

01:32.170 --> 01:33.690
got thrown out with the others.

01:33.890 --> 01:35.780
So come on, pack your shit.
You're leaving now.

01:35.980 --> 01:38.000
Leaving? What you mean, like,
leaving leaving?

01:38.200 --> 01:39.340
That's what the order is.

01:42.260 --> 01:43.260
Time to walk.

01:44.960 --> 01:46.140
What?

01:46.340 --> 01:47.600
What's that for?

01:47.800 --> 01:49.690
[officer] To pack your shit.

01:49.890 --> 01:51.570
I don't give a fuck about
none of this shit. Let's go.

01:52.920 --> 01:55.050
♪ ♪

01:56.490 --> 01:58.410
[laughs]

01:58.610 --> 01:59.890
Uh, excuse me, sir.

02:00.090 --> 02:01.240
Uh, uh, uh, uh,

02:01.440 --> 02:03.030
are you sure y-you meant
Miles Turner

02:03.230 --> 02:05.270
and not Niles Turner?

02:05.470 --> 02:07.160
Miles with an M, dummy.

02:07.360 --> 02:10.140
- Let's go. Come on.
- [laughs]

02:10.340 --> 02:11.470
- Don't you laugh.
- [Miles] Oh, shit.

02:11.670 --> 02:12.820
Don't you laugh. I was--

02:13.020 --> 02:14.690
You're married because of me.

02:14.890 --> 02:16.870
I was practically best man
at your wedding.

02:17.070 --> 02:18.340
Miles!

02:19.340 --> 02:22.150
[soft jazzy music plays]

02:22.350 --> 02:25.210
♪ ♪

02:29.520 --> 02:33.030
[indistinct chatter]

02:33.230 --> 02:36.090
♪ ♪

02:52.370 --> 02:55.370
[snoring]

02:59.510 --> 03:01.430
[person] <i>Okay, let's get it,</i>
<i>health hustlers.</i>

03:01.630 --> 03:03.650
<i>Welcome back to everybody's</i>
<i>favorite,</i>Trap Abs.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.410
Fucking hell.

03:05.610 --> 03:07.830
Happy New Year's Eve, girl.
Hmm.

03:08.030 --> 03:10.380
I forfeited my morning workout
for a week

03:10.580 --> 03:12.050
<i>because I felt sorry for you.</i>

03:12.250 --> 03:13.940
But that's all I can do, girl.

03:14.140 --> 03:15.920
I'm trying to keep it tight.

03:16.120 --> 03:18.540
And you gotta get
your crying ass off my couch.

03:18.740 --> 03:21.170
Mama, you want this basket
of blankets and shit?

03:21.370 --> 03:22.690
No.

03:22.890 --> 03:23.980
I'll look through it.

03:24.180 --> 03:25.800
Just leave
whatever you don't want.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.760
Okay. Yeah, you know,
I don't even really feel like

03:27.960 --> 03:29.760
I need to pack
that much stuff anyway

03:29.960 --> 03:32.090
because Mustafa said the house
is just how I left it.

03:32.290 --> 03:33.770
<i>He's so sweet.</i>[laughs]

03:33.970 --> 03:35.620
But, Mama, please tell me
you gon' leave my room

03:35.820 --> 03:37.470
the way that it is this time.

03:37.670 --> 03:38.970
Hell no.

03:39.170 --> 03:40.380
The second
you move out of there,

03:40.580 --> 03:42.170
I'm renting
that motherfucker out.

03:42.370 --> 03:45.610
Maybe to Ashley to get her
out of my living room.

03:45.810 --> 03:47.720
You and Miles still ain't
said nothing to each other?

03:47.920 --> 03:51.050
No one in the Turner clan
wants to talk to me.

03:51.250 --> 03:53.070
You can't go
into the new year like this.

03:53.270 --> 03:54.920
<i>Work it out.</i>

03:55.120 --> 03:56.140
<i>Today!</i>

03:56.340 --> 03:57.730
<i>So get up.</i>

03:57.930 --> 04:00.770
[somber music plays]

04:00.970 --> 04:03.620
♪ ♪

04:05.840 --> 04:06.920
[Rainey] <i>You sleep?</i>

04:08.270 --> 04:11.230
♪ ♪

04:13.930 --> 04:15.810
- Uh...
- Yes, you do it.

04:16.010 --> 04:17.980
You do it.

04:20.810 --> 04:22.420
Are you gonna
take one over to Mom?

04:23.720 --> 04:25.590
No, I'm not.

04:30.080 --> 04:31.390
Here we go.

04:31.590 --> 04:32.480
[Rainey] <i>Here we go.</i>

04:32.680 --> 04:34.660
Tower of waffles from your dad.

04:34.860 --> 04:36.790
Scooch over.

04:36.990 --> 04:39.470
<i>Trish is gonna have</i>
<i>her girls over tonight</i>

04:39.660 --> 04:42.880
for a little New Year's
celebration, nothing big.

04:43.080 --> 04:45.450
I think we don't need
any more drama.

04:45.650 --> 04:48.600
I think everybody next door
might come too.

04:48.800 --> 04:50.710
- Not her.
- Right.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.000
Hey, kid.

04:54.200 --> 04:56.350
You want to, uh, go hang out
with your mom tonight,

04:56.550 --> 04:58.350
or do you want to stay up late
with me,

04:58.550 --> 05:00.050
<i>Grandma, and Tía Trish</i>

05:00.250 --> 05:02.900
and celebrate New Year's?

05:03.100 --> 05:04.990
Uh, that one.

05:05.190 --> 05:06.540
That one, exactly.

05:06.730 --> 05:08.150
<i>All right, Mom, I gotta go.</i>

05:08.340 --> 05:10.390
Kid, love you.

05:10.590 --> 05:12.120
Love you, Dad.

05:14.080 --> 05:16.330
I'm glad you're home.

05:16.530 --> 05:19.240
[dramatic music plays]

05:19.440 --> 05:22.350
♪ ♪

05:23.090 --> 05:24.480
[phone buzzes]

05:26.310 --> 05:28.840
[indistinct dialogue over TV]

05:29.040 --> 05:30.270
[TV clicks off]

05:33.230 --> 05:34.960
[Marvin over phone]
<i>Hey, son, um,</i>

05:35.150 --> 05:37.940
<i>look, I know you're avoiding</i>
<i>the restaurant,</i>

05:38.140 --> 05:39.890
<i>but, um,</i>

05:40.090 --> 05:42.480
<i>I just had two guys</i>
<i>call out sick.</i>

05:42.680 --> 05:44.680
<i>You can't see me doing</i>
<i>the air-quote thing,</i>

05:44.880 --> 05:47.120
<i>but "sick" from New Year's Ee</i>
<i>shift tonight.</i>

05:47.320 --> 05:49.030
<i>Now, I've only got folks</i>
<i>until 11,</i>

05:49.230 --> 05:51.650
<i>and if you could come work</i>
<i>the kitchen with me,</i>

05:51.850 --> 05:52.990
<i>it would be a big help.</i>

05:53.190 --> 05:54.250
<i>Call me back.</i>

05:55.680 --> 05:58.210
[June] Okay, I just heard it.

06:00.120 --> 06:03.110
And... I am supportive

06:03.310 --> 06:05.910
of however you choose
to respond to it.

06:10.830 --> 06:12.860
He said "with."

06:13.060 --> 06:15.130
"With." He said...

06:15.320 --> 06:17.430
work with him,

06:17.630 --> 06:19.450
not for him.

06:20.840 --> 06:21.850
Why would he say that?

06:22.050 --> 06:23.680
Like...

06:23.880 --> 06:25.610
is he trying to bait me,
or, like, is it, like, a--

06:25.810 --> 06:27.880
[June] I don't--I don't know.
I don't know.

06:28.080 --> 06:30.020
You should find out.

06:33.680 --> 06:34.810
[phone buzzes]

06:40.160 --> 06:41.250
[footsteps tapping]

06:58.660 --> 07:00.490
[engine turning over]

07:19.070 --> 07:20.560
Give it a fucking rest.

07:20.760 --> 07:23.280
What am I supposed to do,
cross the picket line?

07:23.480 --> 07:24.650
You can do that.

07:24.850 --> 07:26.070
Neither one of them
is your kid.

07:26.270 --> 07:27.940
Why are you participating
in their shit?

07:28.140 --> 07:29.590
Just stay out of it.

07:29.790 --> 07:31.620
Someone has to be
in his corner.

07:31.810 --> 07:33.700
One minute,
he's doing a five-year bid.

07:33.900 --> 07:36.450
Next minute, he's getting
walked out of prison.

07:36.650 --> 07:37.970
He's not thinking straight.

07:38.170 --> 07:40.360
He didn't get one instant
to be happy.

07:40.560 --> 07:42.740
He doesn't know what to do
about her.

07:42.930 --> 07:44.610
Can't you see that?

07:44.810 --> 07:46.410
Where's she going?

07:46.610 --> 07:48.180
To see her mom.

07:48.370 --> 07:50.540
Apparently the only one
she's got.

07:52.540 --> 07:54.730
[Marc] <i>Of course, you're not</i>
<i>required to speak, but...</i>

07:54.920 --> 07:57.580
I'd like to encourage you
one more time.

07:57.780 --> 07:59.430
Just the practice
of sharing your feelings

07:59.620 --> 08:01.060
is an important step
in dealing with the trauma

08:01.260 --> 08:02.680
you experienced in prison.

08:05.550 --> 08:07.150
I hear all that.

08:07.350 --> 08:09.630
I'm just gonna, uh--

08:09.830 --> 08:12.350
I'm just gonna listen today.

08:12.550 --> 08:14.180
Well, um--

08:14.380 --> 08:15.250
[door clicks open]

08:15.440 --> 08:16.880
[Earl] Hey, sorry I'm late.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.030
Uh, one of my delivery guys

08:19.230 --> 08:21.160
ate a order again, and I...

08:21.360 --> 08:22.920
<i>I had to remake it.</i>

08:25.750 --> 08:28.390
Anyway, I'm sorry I was--

08:28.590 --> 08:29.800
I was late.

08:30.000 --> 08:30.880
[Marc] <i>No problem, Earl.</i>

08:32.880 --> 08:35.030
<i>So...</i>[sighs]

08:35.230 --> 08:38.050
...today's topic is our
relationship with our families.

08:38.250 --> 08:40.990
Let's, uh--let's try pairing up
and doing a little exercise.

08:41.190 --> 08:43.860
We will face each other

08:44.060 --> 08:45.540
<i>and, when comfortable,</i>

08:45.740 --> 08:47.340
<i>each share how incarceration</i>

08:47.540 --> 08:49.610
<i>has affected our relationshis</i>
<i>with our family,</i>

08:49.810 --> 08:50.730
<i>home life.</i>

08:51.640 --> 08:53.700
Earl...

08:53.900 --> 08:55.940
<i>why don't you pair with our</i>
<i>newest member, Miles?</i>

08:56.140 --> 08:58.420
♪ ♪

08:58.620 --> 09:00.640
[sighs]

09:00.840 --> 09:03.700
♪ ♪

09:23.500 --> 09:24.710
[Rainey] <i>Hey.</i>

09:24.910 --> 09:27.720
♪ ♪

09:34.030 --> 09:35.640
I always loved her spot.

09:37.210 --> 09:38.380
Hey, Genevieve.

09:42.820 --> 09:44.400
Did you know
the "Jirardelli" family crypt

09:44.600 --> 09:46.490
is right over there?

09:46.690 --> 09:48.580
It's huge.

09:48.780 --> 09:50.310
All that chocolate money.

09:53.180 --> 09:55.780
Rainey, just please
let me have this space.

09:55.980 --> 09:58.200
Don't say anything weird
and ruin it for me.

09:58.400 --> 09:59.740
[scoffs] Okay.

09:59.940 --> 10:02.270
- Bye.
- [scoffs] Bye.

10:02.460 --> 10:05.380
You know, Miles' dad
cheated on me for years.

10:05.580 --> 10:07.640
So excuse me if I'm not
hyper-sympathetic

10:07.840 --> 10:09.750
to you getting drunk
and fucking off your marriage

10:09.950 --> 10:11.470
while my son is in prison.

10:11.670 --> 10:14.190
And don't think
I can't hear you thinking,

10:14.390 --> 10:16.020
"It was just a kiss; it's not
like I fucked anybody."

10:16.220 --> 10:18.520
'Cause, you know,
maybe that's true.

10:18.720 --> 10:20.410
I don't actually know or care.

10:20.610 --> 10:21.790
I care about my son.

10:21.980 --> 10:23.960
[laughs]
Yeah, I know, that's it.

10:24.160 --> 10:25.530
What's that, that's it?

10:25.730 --> 10:28.340
"Oh, hey, Ashley,
I'm sort of your mom too."

10:28.530 --> 10:30.580
Yeah, my mom
would've loved that.

10:30.780 --> 10:33.060
I think she would agree
it's not your proudest moment.

10:33.260 --> 10:35.710
Oh, God.

10:35.910 --> 10:38.240
I made a mistake.

10:38.440 --> 10:39.890
And I feel terrible.

10:40.090 --> 10:41.400
Well, good.

10:42.580 --> 10:43.720
Can you just go now?

10:43.920 --> 10:45.220
- No!
- Why not?

10:45.420 --> 10:46.930
Because you are like my kid!

10:49.850 --> 10:52.690
I-I'm here,

10:52.880 --> 10:54.770
trying to make it right
with you, you little shit.

10:54.970 --> 10:57.100
Just fight with me
like you're family.

10:57.300 --> 10:58.210
Fuck you.

10:58.410 --> 10:59.580
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you!

10:59.780 --> 11:00.850
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you!

11:01.050 --> 11:02.560
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you.

11:02.760 --> 11:04.180
You fucked up,

11:04.370 --> 11:06.310
and now this silence
is digging a deeper hole.

11:06.510 --> 11:08.160
He's not talking to me, Rainey.

11:08.360 --> 11:10.790
Oh, he's mad and not talking?
What a shock.

11:10.990 --> 11:12.990
You talk to him.

11:13.190 --> 11:15.360
I don't know what's going on
in his head.

11:15.560 --> 11:16.930
And I want to disappear

11:17.130 --> 11:18.430
because I don't want him
to hate me even more

11:18.630 --> 11:20.910
because I did this to him,
all of it.

11:21.110 --> 11:23.750
I did this all to him,
and I twisted the knife.

11:25.400 --> 11:26.880
And you're
pronouncing it wrong.

11:28.100 --> 11:29.970
What?

11:30.710 --> 11:33.460
It's "Ghirardelli,"
not "Jirardelli."

11:34.760 --> 11:36.210
I don't think that's right.

11:36.410 --> 11:37.990
It's "Ghirardelli."

11:38.190 --> 11:39.360
"Ghirardelli?"

11:39.560 --> 11:40.680
"Ghirardelli."

11:44.210 --> 11:45.600
[Rainey] <i>What happened really?</i>

11:47.340 --> 11:50.480
Rainey, I had a drunk moment...

11:50.680 --> 11:51.560
- No, no, no, not that.
- [Ashley] <i>...and I--</i>

11:52.740 --> 11:54.790
The night Miles got arrested.

11:54.990 --> 11:56.440
Really.

12:01.660 --> 12:03.500
[sighs]

12:03.690 --> 12:05.050
He won't tell me either.

12:06.710 --> 12:08.360
What a fucking pair
you two make.

12:09.840 --> 12:12.760
I just wish he would
say something to me.

12:14.630 --> 12:17.770
He's not coming over to Nancy's
to fix this for you.

12:17.970 --> 12:20.560
You have to stare him down,
say your piece,

12:20.760 --> 12:22.190
and see what happens.

12:22.390 --> 12:25.100
[somber music plays]

12:25.300 --> 12:28.120
♪ ♪

12:37.520 --> 12:39.510
I really don't think
it's "Ghirardelli."

12:39.710 --> 12:42.820
[sniffles] Yeah, it is.
It's "Ghirardelli."

12:43.020 --> 12:45.950
♪ ♪

12:46.150 --> 12:48.610
[indistinct chatter]

12:48.810 --> 12:51.660
♪ ♪

12:56.060 --> 12:57.410
[sighs]

12:58.580 --> 13:01.310
[indistinct chatter]

13:01.510 --> 13:04.370
♪ ♪

13:09.640 --> 13:11.030
[sighs]

13:13.210 --> 13:14.390
Fuck it.

13:14.590 --> 13:16.310
You go, I go?

13:16.510 --> 13:19.530
Uh, nah, I go, you go.

13:19.730 --> 13:22.340
Same time, since we did time
at the same time.

13:22.530 --> 13:25.560
[clock ticking,
lights flickering rhythmically]

13:25.750 --> 13:28.610
♪ ♪

13:34.490 --> 13:36.870
It ain't all bad,
but if it bleeds, it leads.

13:37.070 --> 13:38.240
And I can't tell the difference

13:38.440 --> 13:40.440
between a cell block
and a triage wing.

13:40.640 --> 13:43.420
I got a finite amount
of fortitude in this fortress,

13:43.620 --> 13:46.270
battling the evil gorgeous
of a panopticon,

13:46.470 --> 13:49.170
seen but invisible like
the 13th Amendment tentacle.

13:49.370 --> 13:52.100
Each night might could be you
verse' you in the Octagon.

13:52.300 --> 13:54.650
I'm in crime school
trying to be truant.

13:54.850 --> 13:57.070
How the fuck you think we teach
criminals how to be criminal

13:57.260 --> 13:59.200
here in the fallen god
Parthenon?

13:59.400 --> 14:01.830
I'ma be the paragon prisoner,
dodge all the sinister.

14:02.030 --> 14:03.550
Ms. Understood
been my number one visitor.

14:03.750 --> 14:05.620
And I ain't seen God since Mom
brought the minister.

14:05.820 --> 14:06.840
[Miles] All right, here I go.

14:07.040 --> 14:08.560
I am bench-pressing hard time.

14:08.750 --> 14:10.690
Round-robin family visit
full of fiction.

14:10.890 --> 14:12.580
Smile, don't let them
see your spirit flinching.

14:12.780 --> 14:14.600
Giving the performance
of a lifetime.

14:14.800 --> 14:16.450
Everyone that's coming in
is leaving looking a bit more

14:16.650 --> 14:17.690
like they are living
in the same prison

14:17.890 --> 14:19.460
that we doing a bid in.

14:19.660 --> 14:20.280
Here I am pretending I ain't
tearing down the middle.

14:20.480 --> 14:21.590
I'm a cocked pistol.

14:21.790 --> 14:23.550
I'm a pot boiling over
hot, hot.

14:23.750 --> 14:25.200
<i>They in here with us,</i>
<i>locked in the cell block.</i>

14:25.400 --> 14:26.810
<i>I'm extra baggage for my wif.</i>
<i>I'm a bellhop.</i>

14:27.010 --> 14:28.580
Money on my books used to be
for the nail shop.

14:28.770 --> 14:30.340
Now every penny pinched.

14:30.540 --> 14:32.690
[both] Now I'm a dog in a cage
they can watch age,

14:32.890 --> 14:34.600
they can watch change,
watch become strange,

14:34.800 --> 14:36.600
watch become something
prison sickness made,

14:36.800 --> 14:38.520
a Frankenstein
of the carceral state.

14:38.720 --> 14:40.220
- Whoo.
- Each minute feels like ten.

14:40.420 --> 14:42.150
